# Architectural Diagrams — [ORG_SLUG]

Diagrams live as `.drawio` files (draw.io / diagrams.net format) in this folder.
PNG/SVG exports may be alongside but the source of truth is the `.drawio`.

## Expected diagrams

| File | Description | Required? |
|---|---|---|
| `c4-context-ecosystem.drawio` | C4 Level 1 — [ORG_SLUG] in its ecosystem | Yes |
| `c4-containers-<app>.drawio` | C4 Level 2 — one per app | Per app |
| `deployment-macro.drawio` | Deployment topology (hosts, networks) | Yes |
| `dfd-macro.drawio` | Data flow diagram (level 0) | Yes |
| `security-map-iso-lgpd.drawio` | Security/compliance mapping | If LGPD applies |

## Convention

- Each diagram has a date in the corner: `last updated YYYY-MM-DD`
- Authoritative copy is this repo — copies in slides, wikis are derivatives
- When changing a diagram, also update the corresponding date

## How to view

- Online: open the `.drawio` URL on https://app.diagrams.net/
- VS Code: install the "Draw.io Integration" extension
- Desktop: draw.io desktop app

## Bootstrap state

`/rsct-init-universe` does not create `.drawio` files (they are binary).
Create empty ones manually with draw.io and place here as the org grows.
